			<ns0:name>jvo...@google.com</ns0:name><ns0:uri>/u/102292187274959663599/</ns0:uri></ns0:author><ns0:content type="html">We might also need the pso stub generator to be aware of the size of the original data objects, so that if we end up needing copy relocations, it will allocate the right size in the BSS section of the dynamic executable.

E.g., when I do readelf -r on scons-out/nacl-x86-64-glibc/staging/ppapi_messaging_x86-64.nexe, I do see a copy relocation for __environ.

000011020000  000c00000005 R_X86_64_COPY     0000000011020000 __environ + 0
